{
  "stem": "1895.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 284.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Whoever gets there, our mothers, fathers, sisters, brothers, they're all poisoned and that is their end.' After Jacob had learned the truth, he escaped from Treblinka by burying himself in a truck full of clothing and other loot taken from the victims, and made his way back to Czestochowa where he still had close family.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "When he arrived there, he told the others what he had seen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "No one believed him, not even his own father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Out of anger and frustration, Jacob volunteered for Blizyn.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "He stopped telling the story, except to people like me, whom he befriended and liked.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "He said I was one of the very few who believed him.' [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] This was my introduction to the real purpose, to the real thing of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "After I heard the story from Jacob, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I could no longer delude myself.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Everything fell into place, you might say, because what I'd witnessed and what I saw, even at this tender age of 16 or 15 at the time, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I just understood that this is the way it had to be.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And actually that period was also one of the worst in my life, because at that period, I began to say Kaddish after my parents, because that was a time when I really-- when I really believed that they were dead.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Up until that time, I still deluded myself that it's possible they may be alive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was a turning point in my life in the camps.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I knew then that I was probably all alone on the world at that point.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at first.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I tell you, what gave me the desire to survive was something else.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
